Class ImagePrototype

  com.streetsofboston.smugmug.v1_2_1.system.PrototypeHelper<Image>
      com.streetsofboston.smugmug.v1_2_1.ImagePrototype
All Implemented Interfaces:
ISmugObjectPrototype<Image>
public class ImagePrototype
extends com.streetsofboston.smugmug.v1_2_1.system.PrototypeHelper<Image>
implements ISmugObjectPrototype<Image>

Use this class to create instances of Image or to retrieve them from the Smugmug repository. For example:
ImagePrototype ipt = new ImagePrototype(session);
InputStream is = getClass().getClassLoader().getResourceAsStream("pic.jpg");
ipt.data().read(is);
ipt.data().setAlbum(someAlbum);
ipt.data().setCaption("Image Caption");
ipt.data().setFileName("testimage.jpg");
Image img = ipt.create();

Author:
Anton Spaans

create

public Image create()
             throws SmugmugException
Description copied from interface: ISmugObjectPrototype
Creates a new object of type T given the data as returned by 'data()'. It will add this new smugmug object to the Smugmug repository.
The new object that is created, is always created for the current session-account with which the caller has logged-in.
Session mySession = Session.login("my@mail.com","passwd");
Session forOtherUser = mySession.forOtherAccount("peter", null);
// Return all my albums
AlbumPrototype apMine = new AlbumPrototype(mySession);
AlbumPrototype apPeters = new AlbumPrototype(forOtherUser);
...
...
apMine.create() // Creates album for my@mail.com.
apPeters.create() // Creates album for my@mail.com as well, not for 'peter'.

Specified by:
create in interface ISmugObjectPrototype<Image>
Returns:
A new object of type T.
Throws:
SmugmugException
See Also:
Creates an image with the given data in the prototype.
The binary data in the ImageData attribute is used and uploaded as the image into the Smugmug repository. Note that after calling this method successfully, getImageData will return null (to preserve memory).

get

public Image get(int ID)
          throws SmugmugException
Description copied from class: com.streetsofboston.smugmug.v1_2_1.system.PrototypeHelper
This method implements the ISmugObjectPrototype.get(ID) for (almost) all types of Smugmug objects. It calls 'getAll()' to make sure all the objects of type T are fetched from the Smugmug repository (or cache) and returns the one with the given ID.
